[32;1m[1;3mThe patch in the newer version changes the visibility of the method `createProfileBreakdown()` in `QueryProfiler` from `protected` to `private`. The method returns a new instance of `QueryProfileBreakdown`.

In the older version at ref b4ce56b897c9e0a1a78c2a95ebe264bb1e780ad4, the class `QueryProfiler` is very minimal and does not contain the `createProfileBreakdown()` method. Instead, `QueryProfiler` extends `AbstractProfiler` which has an abstract method `createProfileBreakdown()`.

From the git history and viewcode, it is evident that the `createProfileBreakdown()` method is defined as an abstract method in `AbstractInternalProfileTree` and implemented in `QueryProfiler` in the newer version. The older version does not have this method implemented in `QueryProfiler`.

The patch is about changing the visibility from `protected` to `private` for the method `createProfileBreakdown()` in `QueryProfiler`. However, in the older version, this method is not implemented in `QueryProfiler` at all.

Hence, the patch is adding a new method `createProfileBreakdown()` in `QueryProfiler` which returns a new instance of `QueryProfileBreakdown`. The only difference in the patch is the visibility change from `protected` to `private`.

We can backport this patch by adding the method `createProfileBreakdown()` with `private` visibility in the `QueryProfiler` class in the older version. The rest of the class remains unchanged.

